Cell.Text: Well now that's an odd question. Why in the world would you be asking?

Node.Caption: MG06MirabelleStage10BranchTopic: Do you know anything about the Staff of Magnus?

Cell.Text: [S] I see. Well yes, I suppose I did mention it, though I'm not sure what he expects me to tell you. | I only brought it to his attention a few months back when the Synod showed up here looking for it. | They were apparently under the impression we were keeping it in a closet somewhere.

Node.Caption: MG06Stage10MirabelleReason1: Arch-Mage Aren said you'd mentioned it recently.

Cell.Text: The "Eye of Magnus"? | I can appreciate that this... thing, this Orb... It's very impressive. Very unique, and definitely worth studying. | But let's not jump to any conclusions, or assign it importance beyond what we're certain of.

Node.Caption: MG06Stage10MirabelleReason2: It may be connected to the Eye of Magnus.

Cell.Text: [S] Well, it's said to be very powerful. Has the capacity to store an incredible amount of magical power, as the story goes. | But it's more myth than anything at this point. I've no doubt that it actually exists, but no one has seen it in what, decades? Longer? I'm not sure. | The only time I've heard it mentioned was when those Synod characters showed up some months ago looking for it.

Node.Caption: MG06Stage10MirabelleEyeResponse1: Sorry. So, the Staff of Magnus?

Cell.Text: The Augur? | Just what have you gotten yourself involved in? | Whatever is going on, whatever you're up to... Be very careful.

Node.Caption: MG06Stage10MirabelleEyeResponse2: The Augur referred to it as the Eye of Magnus, not me.

Cell.Text: Mages based out of Cyrodiil. They fancy themselves the Imperial Authority on magic these last few hundred years. | My understanding is that all they really do is make noise in an attempt to curry favor from the Emperor. Lots of politics, little magic. | I was quite surprised to find them on our doorstep. They seemed amiable enough, but their line of questioning made me... uneasy. | It became clear they're trying to hoard powerful artifacts, looking to consolidate power.

[S] No one here does. | The Synod seemed convinced it was somewhere in Skyrim. They inquired about the ruins of Mzulft, but that's all I remember. | It sounded like they were heading there, though they were rather secretive about why. | I suppose if you're intent on looking for the staff, there's a chance they might be in Mzulft yet. Just don't expect them to be cooperative.

Node.Caption: MG06Stage10MirabelleSynodStaff1: So no one knows the Staff's location?

Cell.Text: Really? | Well, I do recall warning them it might not be the safest of locations. I hope this doesn't become a problem for us. | Were you able to learn anything?

Node.Caption: MG06MirabelleStage30BranchTopic: I found the Synod in Mzulft. They're dead.

Cell.Text: Hmm. I can't say I've any idea what they were up to. Have you found this observatory? | You might be able to learn something from it. Keep looking, but be careful.

Node.Caption: MG06Stage30MirabelleResponse1: I found notes about a crystal, and the Oculory in Mzulft.

Cell.Text: I can't imagine what that might be, but if it's safe, you might see if they were successful. | You could get some useful information about whatever they were up to. Sounds like it won't be of use to them now, anyway.

Node.Caption: MG06Stage30MirabelleResponse2: They were trying to perform some sort of experiment, I think.

Cell.Text: I warned them it might be dangerous. It's not my fault they didn't listen. | As long as the Synod don't blame us for this mess, I have more pressing matters to deal with.

Node.Caption: MG06Stage30MirabelleFollowUp1: You don't care that they're dead?

Cell.Text: I'm not really sure. Made and used by Magnus himself, if you believe those sorts of things. | I believe I've heard it said that it's the only thing that could adequately contain his power. | The sort of embellishment wizards of ancient times loved to make.

Node.Caption: MG06MirabelleStaffExtraInfoTopic: What else can you tell me about the Staff of Magnus?
